Justice overlaps with freedom and can be formatted as an input of freedom.

div.div:
Even though 'exploiting criminals' may feel good and be slightly acceptable and is certainly better than being a criminal, it's still good to identify alternatives and optimizations even if they're slightly more work, such as identifying ways to invalidate the inputs of crime, like algorithms to identify criminals or algorithms to distribute resources fairly.
Occasionally an optimization will even be the same level of difficulty as a crime.
